The paper deals with alias analysis, which is a program analysis technique used in programming languages and compilers. Therefore, cs.PL (Programming Languages) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with parallel programming, which falls under cs.AR (Architecture) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper mentions the use of the proposed technique in Proof-Carrying Code (PPC), which is a technique for ensuring program safety, falling under cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper proposes a probabilistic approach, which involves probability theory and statistics, falling under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
